<p>
	Welcome to the Garden Manager, useful for tracking Gardeners, their work, and the Garden Beds to which they tend.
</p>



<table>
	<tr>
		<td>👨‍🌾</td>
		<th>GARDENER</th>
		<td> One who gardens. May have access to different SITEs (many-to-many relationship). A WORKSHIFT is performed by one GARDENER.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>🏡</td>
		<th>SITE</th>
		<td> A location at which a GARDENER works and which may have multiple garden BEDs (one-to-many relationship).</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>🔑</td>
		<th>GARDEN_SITE ACCESS</th>
		<td> A relationship between GARDENERs and SITES (many to many). Indicates whether a gardener has access to the SITE.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>⏱</td>
		<th>WORKSHIFT</th>
		<td> An period of time on a specific date that a GARDENER works on a SITE.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>🌱</td>
		<th>GARDEN BED</th>
		<td> A plot of land located at a SITE which may have multiple PLANTS (an entity not supported by this website).</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<table>
	<tr>
		<td>🔭</td>
		<th>BedMap</th>
		<td> A filter feature that allows one to view all Garden Beds located on a Site. A graphical map view is generated.</td>
	</tr>
</table>